# CSS And Style Reuse

- Identify repeated class strings or style objects before adding more copies.
- If a class combination is used three or more times in one component, extract a local constant near the top of the file.
- If a class combination is reused across components, move it to a shared style module, design token, theme extension, or custom utility.
- Name extracted styles by intent, not appearance alone, for example `primaryButton` or `formInput`.
- Prefer the project’s established styling system over introducing a new one.
- Update all affected usages when consolidating repeated styles.
